title: Kazumi Kishi
text:
is a former <a href="Japan">Japan</a>ese <a href="Association%20football">football</a> player. She played for <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a>.
Club career.
Kishi was born on November 25, 1975. She played for <a href="Urawa%20Reds%20Ladies">Urawa Reinas FC</a>.
National team career.
On May 21, 1998, Kishi debuted for <a href="Japan%20women%27s%20national%20football%20team">Japan national team</a> against <a href="United%20States%20women%27s%20national%20soccer%20team">United States</a>. She played at <a href="Football%20at%20the%201998%20Asian%20Games">1998 Asian Games</a>. She played 9 games and scored 2 goals for Japan until 2001.
